A 35-year-old man is expected to appear in the Rustenburg Magistrate s Court on Wednesday for possession of nyaope with an estimated street value of R84 000. Nyaope is a highly addictive drug consisting of dagga, heroin, anti-retro-viral drugs, rat poison and acid. Police spokesperson Colonel Emelda Setlhako said the man was arrested in Seraleng near Rustenburg on Friday. According to information, the police executed a search warrant at the suspect s place and that led to a major breakthrough in the fight against substance abuse when 1 684 packets of nyaope with estimated street value of R84 000 were found inside the house. The police also found cash amount of R16 000 during the search. The suspect was arrested for possession of drugs. African News Agency (ANA)